cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.NE 

This paper focuses on improving named entity recognition on social media texts, specifically Turkish tweets. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves experiments and evaluation, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with social media texts, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
